MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From south Entrance Station at Great Sand Dunes National Park, drive north 1.58 miles on main Park road to intersection of Primitive Medano Pass Rd (4WD required).  Follow this road, which will cross Medano Creek at just over 4 miles. Go another 0.16 miles to an administrative road (Closed to Public), which heads in a westerly direction. Park.  Follow this road on foot 0.96 miles to the crossing of the Sand Ramp Trail and Little Medano Creek -- this is the sample site.

From south Entrance Station at Great Sand Dunes National Park, drive north 1.58 miles on main Park road to intersection of Primitive Medano Pass Rd (4WD required).  Follow this road, which will cross Medano Creek at just over 4 miles. Go another 2.05 miles, crossing the creek 3 additional times.  The sample site is the segment of the stream in the severely burned riparian area, which is west of the road about 100 feet below a beaver dam.

From south Entrance Station at Great Sand Dunes National Park, drive north 1.58 miles on main Park road to intersection of Primitive Medano Pass Rd (4WD required).  Follow this road to the first crossing of Medano Creek at just over 4 miles. Sample site is about 100' upstream of the crossing.
